## Review: T7.1 — Add integration test for `--once` snapshot output

**Reviewer:** sigma | **Claimed by:** phi | **FP ref:** FP-WPPS-T7

---

### Findings (severity order)

**[suggestion] Missing exec timeout — test hangs if binary hangs**
`tests/integration/waveplan_ps_test.go:32`

`exec.Command` is used without a context. If `--once` regresses to blocking (e.g., enters the live watcher instead of exiting), the test hangs indefinitely. Fix:

```go
ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)
defer cancel()
run := exec.CommandContext(ctx, binaryPath, "--once", ...)
```

**[suggestion] Merged stdout/stderr hides output-routing bugs**
`tests/integration/waveplan_ps_test.go:40-43`

Both streams are captured into the same buffer (`run.Stderr = &stdout`). If `runOnce` accidentally writes the snapshot to stderr instead of stdout, every assertion still passes. Separate them:

```go
var stdout, stderr bytes.Buffer
run.Stdout = &stdout
run.Stderr = &stderr
// assert on stdout.String() only; fail on stderr.String() != ""
```

**[nit] `--log-dir` points to fixture root, not the actual log directory**
`tests/integration/waveplan_ps_test.go:29,38`

Logs are written to `fixtureRoot/.waveplan/logs/` but `--log-dir fixtureRoot` is passed. This works because `DiscoverLogs` uses recursive `filepath.WalkDir` (confirmed in `discovery/discover.go:85`). But it's non-obvious; passing `logDir` directly would make the coupling explicit.

**[nit] Fresh `GOCACHE` per test run forces full recompile**
`tests/integration/waveplan_ps_test.go:19`

```go
build.Env = append(os.Environ(), "GOCACHE="+filepath.Join(t.TempDir(), "gocache"))
```

`t.TempDir()` is cleaned up after each run, so the cache is never reused. Drop the GOCACHE override to allow incremental builds across runs.

